'.\" -*- nroff -*-
.TH KAFS-INFO 8 "2026-03-17" "kafs 0.4.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
kafs-info \- print offline KAFS image superblock, tombstone, HRL, and tail metadata summary
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kafs-info
.I image
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kafs-info
opens a KAFS image read-only and prints basic metadata, including:
.IP \[bu] 2
superblock magic/version and block geometry,
.IP \[bu] 2
inode/block counters,
.IP \[bu] 2
tombstone inode count and oldest deletion timestamp,
.IP \[bu] 2
hash settings,
.IP \[bu] 2
HRL index/entry region summary,
.IP \[bu] 2
tail metadata region state, offset, and size.
.PP
For format version 5 images,
.B kafs-info
reports whether the dedicated tail metadata region is enabled and prints its
byte offset and byte size as part of the top-level summary.
.PP
This command does not modify image contents.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Completed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
I/O or parse error.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kafs (1),
.BR kafsctl (1),
.BR mkfs.kafs (8),
.BR fsck.kafs (8),
.BR kafsdump (8),
.BR kafsimage (8),
.BR kafsresize (8)
.SH AUTHOR
kafs project.
